cs.NE, cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a variant of differential evolution, which is a popular evolutionary algorithm used in optimization problems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper deals with the evolution of a population of agents, which can be seen as a control problem. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) is a possible category as the paper applies the proposed algorithm to space trajectory optimization, which can be seen as an engineering problem. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes an algorithm that performs better than standard DE on some optimization problems. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the optimization of trajectories, which can be relevant in robotics applications.
